      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Leaning to GOODNESS (6) who ran a good race on debut at Bendigo over 1300m when in the market there and battled on strongly for a narrow third after getting back in the field. She gave every indication the rise in trip would suit nicely and with natural upside and a good draw she can get the job done. JUST FOR KICKS (2) is a clear danger. He's placed in all three runs to date and should be hard fit. He's a touch more exposed but by the same token is also more experienced and this looks a nice race. OBON (3) is knocking on the door with back-to-back runner-up efforts, he should land on speed here and prove hard to run down. ROYAL MAXIMUS (4) showed improvement at start two when placing at Ballarat and can continue to progress. DUNTULM LASS (5) got home well at Sale and is in the mix.",
